    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-13T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="847"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d847">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 124.62/39</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJE1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-13T22:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1917, 10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 13, 7 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>350. Foreign Office informs me Spanish Ambassador, Berlin officially took charge
                    American interests February 6, but that owing to presence of American Ambassador
                    and staff he only actually took charge and opened special office for American
                    interests February 12. Spanish Ambassador states that Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_GJW1">Gerard</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_GJC1"
                        >Grew</persName> asked him to employ Vice Consul <persName>Von
                        Versen</persName> to assist in connection with American interests.
                        <persName>Versen</persName> is American citizen but German by birth and
                    Spanish Ambassador asks to be informed as soon as possible whether Department
                    would wish him to be employed under the circumstances.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d847fn1">Assent to his employment temporarily given in telegram of
                        Feb. 16 (No. 259) to the Ambassador. Same file number; not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
